Provides extensions of JNA libraries for Windows.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary

    Kernel32
    Kernel32 and WinNT info submitted to JNA as #1050.
    PowrProf
    Power profile stats.
    PowrProf.POWER_INFORMATION_LEVEL
    Indicates power level information.

    WinNT.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Kernel32Util
    Kernel32Util.
    PowrProf.ProcessorPowerInformation
    Contains information about a processor.
    PowrProf.SystemBatteryState
    Contains information about the current state of the system battery.
    ProcInfo
    Temporary test case to verify code behaves as expected.
    VersionHelpers
    The following functions can be used to determine the current operating system version or identify whether it is a Windows or Windows Server release.
    WinNT.CACHE_RELATIONSHIP
    Describes cache attributes.
    WinNT.GROUP_AFFINITY
    Represents a processor group-specific affinity, such as the affinity of a thread.
    WinNT.GROUP_RELATIONSHIP
    Represents information about processor groups.
    WinNT.NUMA_NODE_RELATIONSHIP
    Represents information about a NUMA node in a processor group.
    WinNT.PROCESSOR_GROUP_INFO
    Represents the number and affinity of processors in a processor group.
    WinNT.PROCESSOR_RELATIONSHIP
    Describes the logical processors associated with either a processor core or a processor package.
    WinNT.SYSTEM_LOGICAL_PROCESSOR_INFORMATION_EX
    Contains information about the relationships of logical processors and related hardware.

Package oshi.jna.platform.windows Description

Provides extensions of JNA libraries for Windows. These classes should be considered non-API as they may be removed if/when their code is incorporated into the JNA project.
